##


4.3.1 — Discrete Geometry Enhancement Blueprint
Pre‑Differential Geometry Fortification Layer

I. Formalizing the Glyph as a Simplicial Complex
RCFT Definition: A glyph 
𝐺
 is a finite, oriented simplicial complex:

𝐺
=
⋃
𝑘
=
0
𝑑
Σ
𝑘
where:

Σ
0
 = set of vertices 
𝑣
𝑖
 (glyph anchors)

Σ
1
 = set of edges 
[
𝑣
𝑖
,
𝑣
𝑗
