These are not decorative equations — they are reproducibility gates. On canonical testbeds (e.g., the two‑tet interior), each identity is evaluated; if residuals exceed tolerance, the expansion fails certification.

4.3.x — Topology Audit
Every flux, every holonomy, every “measurement” must be traceable to a topological generator.

