4.3.x — Discipline Packet
The expansion concludes by emitting a discipline packet — a compact YAML record that self‑certifies the run:

yaml
geometry_expansion:
  mesh_id: <hash>
  metric_tolerances:
    edge_length: 1e-8
    face_area: 1e-8
    volume: 1e-10
  connection_tolerances:
    holonomy_phase: 1e-9
  operator_tolerances:
    gauss_residual: 1e-12
    faraday_residual: 1e-12
    ampere_residual: 1e-12
  topology_audit:
    Zk_basis: <sparse_repr>
    Bk_basis: <sparse_repr>
  status: PASS
This packet is not optional. It is the receipt of reality for the expansion — without it, no result is archived, no claim is made.





